This code was used in the Physical Review E paper titled "Driven Lorentz Gas Model in the Discrete Time Domain" by Dan Shafir, Alessio Squarcini, Stanislav Burov, and Thomas Franosch (accepted on April 23, 2025).
If you use this code in your work, please cite the above article.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
sim_obstacles_response.py

code is in python using the numpy library. This generates the simulations data for Figures 2, 4, and 8.
Note the code does not need to be efficent for large step numbers.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The c code usues the random number generator library 
 SFMT ver. 1.5
 SIMD oriented Fast Mersenne Twister(SFMT)

-- see documentation online

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

simulation for small number of steps - used to generate the data for figures 5 and 6

small_N_sim.c
